    <subfield code="y">00005 (Color online) Evolution of kinetic energy and density within a spherical volume of radius $R_{c}$. By fitting the data for the kinetic energy with an exponential decay function $E_{kin}(t) = A\cdot \exp(K\cdot t) + b$ the relaxation time $\tau_{c} = K^{-1}$ can be obtained. The results are (A, K, b)$=$(1.3195, 7.4640e-4, 1.1124) with squared diagonal elements of the covariance matrix (6.8294e-7, 3.7630e-19, 8.5889e-11) in units of ($\epsilon$, $0.0025\cdot\tau$, $\epsilon$).</subfield>
